{"SCELERAT":[{"def":"A villian; a criminal.","pos":""}],"SCELESTIC":[{"def":"Evil; wicked; atrocious.","pos":""}],"SCELET":[{"def":"A mummy; a skeleton.","pos":""}],"SCENARIO":[{"def":"A preliminary sketch of the plot, or main incidents, of an opera.","pos":""}],"SCENE":[{"def":"The structure on which a spectacle or play is exhibited; the part of a theater in which the acting is done, with its adjuncts and decorations; the stage.","pos":""},{"def":"The decorations and fittings of a stage, representing the place in which the action is supposed to go on; one of the slides, or other devices, used to give an appearance of reality to the action of a play; as, to paint scenes; to shift the scenes; to go behind the scenes.","pos":""}],"SCENEFUL":[{"def":"Having much scenery.","pos":""}],"SCENEMAN":[{"def":"The man who manages the movable scenes in a theater.","pos":""}],"SCENERY":[{"def":"Assemblage of scenes; the scenes of a play; the disposition and arrangement of the scenes in which the action of a play, poem, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"Sum of scenes or views; general aspect, as regards variety and beauty or the reverse, in a landscape; combination of natural views, as woods, hills, etc.","pos":""}],"SCENESHIFTER":[{"def":"One who moves the scenes in a theater; a sceneman.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to scenery; of the nature of scenery; theatrical.","pos":""}],"SCENOGRAPH":[{"def":"A perspective representation or general view of an object.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to scenography; drawn in perspective.","pos":""}],"SCENOGRAPHY":[{"def":"The art or act of representing a body on a perspective plane; also, a representation or description of a body, in all its dimensions, as it appears to the eye.","pos":""}],"SCENT":[{"def":"To perceive by the olfactory organs; to smell; as, to scent game, as a hound does.","pos":""},{"def":"To imbue or fill with odor; to perfume.","pos":""}],"SCENTFUL":[{"def":"Full of scent or odor; odorous.","pos":""},{"def":"Of quick or keen smell.","pos":""}],"SCENTLESS":[{"def":"Having no scent.","pos":""}],"SCEPSIS":[{"def":"Skepticism; skeptical philosophy.","pos":""},{"def":"To endow with the scepter, or emblem of authority; to invest with royal authority.","pos":""}],"SCEPTERELLATE":[{"def":"Having a straight shaft with whorls of spines; -- said of certain sponge spicules.","pos":""},{"def":"Having no scepter; without authority; powerless; as, a scepterless king.","pos":""}],"SCEPTRAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a scepter; like a scepter.","pos":""}],"SCERN":[{"def":"To discern; to perceive.","pos":""}]}